                  ( UFW firewall )
sudo ufw status                            ( Check the status )
sudo ufw enable                           ( If itâ€™s inactive, enable it: )
sudo ufw allow from 203.0.113.25          ( This allows all ports for that IP )
sudo ufw allow from 203.0.113.25 to any port 22  ( This allows that IP to access SSH (port 22) only.)
sudo ufw deny from 203.0.113.25            ( To block all traffic from a specific IP:)
sudo ufw deny from 203.0.113.25 to any port 80  ( This blocks that IP from accessing HTTP (port 80).)
sudo ufw status numbered                    ( To delete a rule, first list them:)
sudo ufw delete 2                           ( Then delete the rule by number:)



                  ( CSF Firewall )

ðŸ§¾ Important Files & Commands
Function	                Command / File
Install CSF	              wget https://download.configserver.com/csf.tgz â†’ extract and run sh install.sh
Config file              	/etc/csf/csf.conf
Start/Stop firewall	      csf -e / csf -x
Check status	            csf -l
Allow IP                	csf -a <IP>
Deny IP	                  csf -d <IP>
Remove IP	                  csf -r
Test mode                 (default after install)	TESTING = "1" â†’ change to 0 in csf.conf for full protection
